OL,3,CProsecutors to contest 'unduly
OL,4,Clenient' sentence for exploitation
OL,6,FProsecutors are to appeal against a
OL,7,Fseven-year sentence handed to a
OL,8,Fpensioner who exploited vulnerable
OL,9,Fyoung women by supplying them with
OL,10,Fheroin in exchange for them working as
OL,11,Fprostitutes.
OL,13,FOliver James MacCormack, 71, was
OL,14,Fsentenced at Belfast Crown Court last
OL,15,Fmonth, having previously pleaded
OL,16,Fguilty to 40 offences, including
OL,17,Fcharges of human trafficking and
OL,18,Fcontrolling prostitution.
