OL,3,CProsecutors to contest 'unduly
OL,4,Clenient' sentence for exploitation
OL,6,FA PPS spokesperson said: "While
OL,7,Fsentencing is a matter for the
OL,8,Findependent judiciary, the Director of
OL,9,FPublic Prosecutions does have the
OL,10,Fpower to refer particular sentences to
OL,11,Fthe Court of Appeal on the grounds
OL,12,Fthat they may be unduly lenient.
OL,14,F"An unduly lenient sentence is one
OL,15,Fthat falls outside the range of
OL,16,Fsentences that a judge, taking into
OL,17,Fconsideration all relevant factors and
OL,18,Fhaving regard to sentencing guidance,
OL,19,Fcould reasonably impose.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUvD@AOU
